        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Service procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Batteries expel explosive gases. Keep sparks, flames, burning cigarettes or other ignition
                        sources away at all times. Always wear safety glasses and a face shield when working near
                        batteries to avoid personal injury or death.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent unexpected movement of the vehicle and possible serious personal injury or death,
                        park the vehicle on a flat, level surface, set the parking brake, turn the engine off, and chock
                        the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>To repair a battery box that has broken loose from the floor mounting location, the following
                procedure should be followed.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0747022" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0747022.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="432px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Standard Group 31 Battery Installation, Single Strap Repair</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0747023" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0747023A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="432px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Dual 8D Battery Installation, Dual Strap Repair</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean the surface of the floor sills and floor panels where support brackets are to be
                    mounted.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate support brackets and weld in place - refer to Figure 2 and 3 for bracket
                    placement. See parts kit for welding instructions.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Before installing the support strap assembly, inspect the existing welds on the battery
                    box assembly, door and frame assembly and the battery box support clips on the rear lip of the box.
                    If these welds are cracked or broken, they must be repaired. If the battery box support clips are
                    missing, they must be installed.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the support strap assembly (2590995c1) to the battery box assembly by aligning
                    the tee bolts in the support strap assembly with the slots in the support bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the flange nut (414087c1) on the tee bolts of the support strap assembly and
                    tighten securely (35-40 Lbf-ft.)
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
